## Tributary Use Pledge, §6

In addition to the SSPL, any use of this work in a service offered
to the public (whether as SaaS, API, hosted platform, or otherwise)
that competes with, replicates, or commercially exploits the Liana
Banyan Platform's substrate-benchmark methodology or the Staggered
Swarm pipeline requires:

1. Full open-sourcing of your competing service stack under SSPL.
2. Attribution to Liana Banyan Corporation in any published results,
   papers, or derivative benchmarks.
3. A canonical citation to the original release:
   Liana Banyan Corporation. (2026). Substrate benchmark:
   per-domain Staggered Swarm methodology. bp077-substrate-proof-v1.
   https://github.com/Upekrithen/LianaBanyanPlatform/releases/tag/bp077-substrate-proof-v1

Internal research, academic reproduction, and non-commercial benchmarking
are permitted under standard SSPL terms without the §6 trigger.

"Designed-to-be-Copied" -- the kit ships with the intent that anyone
can reproduce the results. Reproduction is encouraged. Commercial
exploitation without open-sourcing your stack is not.

-- Liana Banyan Corporation, 2026-06-07
